**Overview**

This dashboard shows an overview of HTTP, RDP, DHCP, SMB, SSH, FTP and Network File related activity on the network.

Please visit the [HTTP](https://schema.ocsf.io/1.1.0/classes/http_activity), [DHCP](https://schema.ocsf.io/1.1.0/classes/dhcp_activity), [RDP](https://schema.ocsf.io/1.1.0/classes/rdp_activity), [SMB](https://schema.ocsf.io/1.1.0/classes/smb_activity), [SSH](https://schema.ocsf.io/1.1.0/classes/ssh_activity), [FTP](https://schema.ocsf.io/1.1.0/classes/ftp_activity), [Network File Activity](https://schema.ocsf.io/1.1.0/classes/network_file_activity) documentation for more information.

JVM 

This dashboard provides visibility into the JVM runtime environment powering Kafka.

- Tracks JVM uptime, version details, loaded classes, and active thread counts.  
- Monitors heap and non-heap memory usage, memory pools, and buffer pools.

#### Description

This dashboard provides comprehensive visibility into sensor health status within the Nozomi Networks platform using the Health data stream.

It visualizes health events by sensor appliance type to highlight which categories of devices are generating the most alerts. A table displays the top 10 sensor hosts with the highest volume of health events, helping identify sensors that may require immediate attention. A saved search presents essential sensor details including timestamp, sensor ID, host name, and appliance type to support proactive monitoring and troubleshooting efforts.

This dashboard provides detailed visibility into user and system activity within the Nozomi Networks platform using the Audit data stream. 

It displays audit events by action type and controller to highlight the most common operations and their associated modules. Visualizations also include browser usage distribution, trends of audit activity over time, and actions grouped by user to support behavior analysis. A table lists the top 10 source IP addresses to help identify frequent origin points for system access. A saved search provides essential audit details including timestamp, event name, action, browser, username, controller, and IP address to support auditing, investigations, and compliance tracking.

#### Description

This dashboard provides visibility into alert activity within the Nozomi Networks platform using the Alert data stream.

It includes metrics for open, closed, and acknowledged alerts, with trends over time. The dashboard highlights top high-risk alerts and threats, and shows alert distribution by protocol and event type. A saved search displays essential alert details for investigation.

#### Description

This dashboard provides comprehensive visibility into asset distribution within the Nozomi Networks platform using the Assets data stream.

It shows metrics for IT, OT, and IoT assets by technology category and name. High-risk assets (risk  40) are highlighted by type and vendor. The dashboard also includes asset distribution by OS, vendor, zone, and protocol. A saved search displays essential asset details to support monitoring and investigation.

#### Description

This dashboard provides visibility into node distribution within the Nozomi Networks platform using the Node data stream.

It includes metrics for total, public, and private nodes, with visualizations by OS, type, vendor, zone, and role. The dashboard highlights the top node protocols and VLAN IDs. A saved search displays essential node details to support asset tracking and analysis.

This dashboard provides visibility into vulnerabilities within the Nozomi Networks platform using the Node CVE data stream.

It shows total, resolved, and unresolved CVEs, with trends over time. Vulnerabilities are categorized by type and CWE, and high-severity CVEs are highlighted. A saved search displays key CVE details to support risk assessment and remediation.

**Session**  
[Variable](#/dashboard/nozomi_networks-1b267947-931d-484b-bf52-52981e3c7a72)  

#### Description

This dashboard provides comprehensive insights into network session activity within the Nozomi Networks platform using the Session data stream. 

It displays key metrics for total sessions to monitor real-time network usage. Sessions are broken down by protocol and transport protocol to identify the types of traffic traversing the network. Line charts show trends in transferred bytes and packets over time, helping track bandwidth consumption and detect anomalies. Tables highlight the top 10 source IPs, destination IPs, and VLAN IDs to support threat hunting and network segmentation analysis. A saved search presents essential session attributes including timestamp, session ID, status, zones, protocols, and VLAN ID to assist with investigation and operational monitoring.

attributes.description: Get all current network connections.
Get all services and exclude the ones running under Service User Accounts. Services running under regular user contexts are uncommon and can indicate lateral movement or persistence.
attributes.query:
SELECT description, display_name, name, path, pid, service_type, start_type, status, user_account FROM services
WHERE NOT (user_account LIKE "%LocalSystem" OR user_account LIKE "%LocalService" OR user_account LIKE "%NetworkService" OR user_account == null)

attributes.description: The "TYCHON Endpoint Browser" dashboard provides host visualization data for a single endpoint at a time. The dashboard is a set of several individual views broken down by tabs near the top of the screen. The TYCHON Endpoint Browser - Benchmark Results view displays all Benchmark SCAP scan results for the OS and Software installed.

attributes.description: The "TYCHON Endpoint Browser" dashboard provides host visualization data for a single endpoint at a time. The dashboard is a set of several individual views broken down by tabs near the top of the screen. The TYCHON Endpoint Browser  Hardware Inventory view displays all hardware currently or previously attached to a computer.

attributes.title: [TYCHON] Endpoint Browser - Hardware Inventory

attributes.description: The "TYCHON Endpoint Browser" dashboard provides host visualization data for a single endpoint at a time. The dashboard is a set of several individual views broken down by tabs near the top of the screen. The TYCHON Endpoint Browser  Software Inventory view displays all installed Applications and Products on a computer, its version, and the last time it was seen.

The TYCHON Endpoint Browser  Drives and Disks view displays current Hard Drive and Partitions attached to endpoints at the time TYCHON performed its check.

attributes.title: [TYCHON] Endpoint Browser - Drives and Disks

attributes.description: The "TYCHON Endpoint Browser" dashboard provides host visualization data for a single endpoint at a time. The dashboard is a set of several individual views broken down by tabs near the top of the screen. The TYCHON Endpoint Browser  Network Cards view displays information about every physical and virtual network interface attached to the endpoint. TYCHON also captures wireless identification information, drivers, dhcp/wins server information, and more.

The dashboard is a set of several individual views broken down by tabs near the top of the screen. The TYCHON Endpoint Browser  Vulnerabilities view displays all CVEs checked by TYCHON and reported as passed or failed.

attributes.description: The "TYCHON Endpoint Browser" dashboard provides host visualization data for a single endpoint at a time. The dashboard is a set of several individual views broken down by tabs near the top of the screen. The TYCHON Endpoint Browser  Host Information view displays overall Operating System data and summary information from its subordinate datasets (disks, drives, vulnerabilities, benchmarks, etc.).

attributes.title: [TYCHON] Endpoint Browser - Host Information

attributes.description: The "TYCHON Endpoint Browser" dashboard provides host visualization data for a single endpoint at a time. The dashboard is a set of several individual views broken down by tabs near the top of the screen. The TYCHON Endpoint Browser  Services and Ports view displays all Services found on hosts, as well as listening ports and ARP Tables.
